$ CSS properties transform, transform-box, transform-origin, transform-style

The `transform-*` properties modify the *coordinate space* of the CSS visual formatting model and thus allow to rotate, move, shrink etc. elements.

table { ll
  `transform-box` ☰ `content-box`, `border-box`, `fill-box`, `stroke-box`, `view-box` and «global values» 
  `transform-origin` ☰ `center`, `top left`, `100px 30px` etc.
  `transform-style` ☰ `flat` or `preserve-3d`
table }

`transform` is a *shorthand* property for `transform-box`, `transform-origin` and `transform-style`.


{ Values

  table { ll
     `translate(x, y)`, `translateX(x)`, `translateY(y)`, `translateZ(z)`, `translate3D(x, y, z)` ☰ Compare with the `→ development/web/CSS/properties/translate` property
     `scale(x, y)`, `scaleX(x)`, `scaleY(y)`, `scaleZ(z)`, `scale3d(x, y, z)` ☰
     `rotate(angle)`, `rotateX(a)`, `rotateY(a)`, `rotateZ(a)` ☰ 
     `skew(x, y)`, `skewX(x)`, `skewY(y)` ☰ 
     `perspective(p)` ☰ If used, must be listed first.
     `matrix(a, b, c, d, e, f)`, `matrix3d( … 4x4 elements …)` ☰
     `inherit`, `initial`, `revert`, `revert-layer`, `unset` ☰ *global values*.
  table }

}

